Description: Pre-Owned Watch Inspections & Reports
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: The savvier shoppers among us understand that buying pre-owned luxury watches is the smart way to go. After all, pre-owned fine timepieces already took their biggest depreciation hit when the first buyer left the retail store. And since high-end watches are built to last several lifetimes, the only thing you’re really missing by buying an authentic watch in great condition from the secondary market is the hefty retail price tag.  However, just like any secondary market, there are some precautions to take to ensure that you’re getting your money’s worth. The pre-owned luxury watch space is a robust market with plenty of sources to buy and sell used timepieces. But, how do you know if the seller is a trustworthy one and more importantly, how do you know if the watch you’re buying is the real deal? Enter WatchFacts, a third-party certification program that does all the work for you so you know exactly what you’re buying.   Just like customers depend on Carfax reports to inform them about the history of a used car, WatchFacts provides detailed certification reports about secondhand luxury watches. Using a proprietary grading system and a standardized inspection process, a WatchFacts Report includes a WatchFacts Score, which gives you a quick overview of the overall condition of the watch.  A top WatchFacts Score of 100 indicates that the watch is in unworn/like new condition, followed by different scores for excellent, very good, and so on. Along with the score, a WatchFacts Report provides other essential information such as brand, model, date of production, movement, materials, authenticity check, theft check, current performance, and information about any previous servicing.  Buying from a WatchFacts partner network minimizes your risk when purchasing from the secondary luxury watch market since you’ll have access to a WatchFacts Report. Plus, seeing as WatchFacts’ goal is customer peace of mind, if something goes wrong, WatchFacts will intercede on your behalf so you are content with your purchase.  Shoppers can take advantage of a vast selection of products by buying certified pre-owned luxury watches from Amazon, eBay, and Jomashop. Every watch listed as “Certified Pre-Owned” on Amazon and Jomashop comes with a one-year limited warranty and a WatchFacts Report so you can rest assured that the timepiece delivered to your doorstep will meet all your expectations. Furthermore, pre-owned timepieces offered by Kay Jewelers, Jared, and Zales have all been inspected by WatchFacts.  With a WatchFacts report in hand, buying a pre-owned luxury watch is no longer a guessing game but now it’s a safe, secure, and transparent process.

Full Description: LTC Solution, LLC came into existence in 2006.  They are owners and operators of retirement/assisted living facilities.  They realized the need to gather and maintain records in a consolidated and easy to access format so they could provide their residents with the best care possible.  Costly redundancy and inaccurate copying of information cut down on efficiency and time spent with residents. They searched for a program to address their needs and goals.  Unfortunately they could not find such a program.  Instead they found some good programs that did some of what they needed but none that did it all in an easy to use integrated manner.  Creating their own program allowed us to eliminate duplicate entries, have to learn only one program and have all information flow together.  This freed up their staff's time for the important tasks - being with and caring for their residents. All your information, from prospect to move-in & move-out, from work order to completed tasks, scheduling staff, medication administration, assessments, plan of care, budgeting, invoicing  are in one easy to learn and use program.  Their Management Information Suite is here to  help you run your facility in a cost-effective and efficient manner.

Key features include project management with scheduling, project billing, real-time project updates, account tracking, materials coordination and planning, and document tracking, With ProjectPro, businesses can forecast precise cost projections, manage resources and equipment, monitor inventory and job material levels, view project schedules, and monitor KPIs. Description: VTEL Products Corporation is the global leader in fully integrated, PC-based group videoconferencing systems.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Since inception in 1985 VTEL has been a global leader in providing tens of thousands of PC-based videoconferencing systems for use in distance education, training, and administrative meetings.  The company was the originator of the H.323 videoconferencing standard and originally manufactured a line of traditional codecs that integrated a PC for content-sharing purposes.  With the advent of software-based videoconferencing solutions such as Zoom and Skype for Business the company developed an entirely new architecture in which the CPU itself performs all video and audio compression functions, thus leveraging the inherent performance and affordability advantages of this approach. VTEL was taken public on the NASDAQ exchange in April of 1992.  In early 2002 the VTEL Video Systems Division was taken private and company management subsequently developed the aforementioned product architecture which offers significantly greater performance for end-users at a considerably lower cost.

RentMatch is a new apartment ratings and review service to help renters avoid buyer's remorse and choose the best place to rent. RentMatch combines user generated content and data from publicly available resources like city and county government to provide prospective tenants with everything they should know about a property before they sign a lease. The company does not compete with existing rental listing sites (Craigslist, Rent.com, MyNewPlace, etc.) and does not provide availability information on properties. The company models itself after TripAdvisor and how TripAdvisor passes leads to sites like Expedia or Priceline.
